&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 3 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Clinical Professional (Immunisations)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Registered professional (Immunisations) you will be required to work across the Gwent wide area, vaccinating within any one our community venues including mobile units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience within the field of immunisation, would be an advantage but is not a requirement as full training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be a motivated, autonomous practitioner, able to integrate and work competently within a skill mix team. You should be able to respond to the physical, mental and emotional challenges of working within the Mass Vaccination Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be required to contribute to any other duties which may be requested by the senior nurse in order to facilitate the smooth running of the Mass Vaccinatin Programme. You should be fully committed to your own professional development and ready to undertake specific development required of the role. In return, you will be working within a close, supportive team and will be mentored through education programmes to meet all competencies required to work in this exciting field of nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to meet the geographical needs of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shikala Mansfield - Senior Workforce Business Partner&lt;/p&gt;
